## 🔍 Memory Learning Rules

### **Auto-Detection Triggers**

| Event | Memory Update | Example |
|-------|---------------|---------|
| User generates 3+ prompts | Detect preferred sections | User always has "Constraints" → add to `requiredSections` |
| User deletes same section 2x | Mark as unused | User removes "Background" twice → add to `unusedSections` |
| User expands section 3+ times | Learn expansion preference | User expands "Examples" → flag as `prefers_detailed` |
| User condenses section 3+ times | Learn conciseness preference | User condenses "Intro" → flag as `prefers_concise` |
| User uses same keywords 5+ times | Add to frequent terms | "API", "authentication" → add to `frequentKeywords` |

### **Pattern Detection Logic**

```javascript
// After each session, analyze behavior
class MemoryLearner {
  analyzeSession(sessionData) {
    // Detect section preferences
    if (this.appearsInLast3Sessions('Constraints')) {
      memory.review.requiredSections.push('Constraints');
    }

    // Detect editing patterns
    if (this.expandedSectionType('Examples', 3)) {
      memory.analysis.commonEdits['Examples'] = ['expand', ...];
    }

    // Detect quality bar
    if (this.averageSectionLength() > 700) {
      memory.global.qualityBar = 'comprehensive';
    }
  }
}
```

